---
/**
 * IobSettingsScreen — Settings › IOB Display. The opt-in toggle is DEFAULT OFF,
 * with a plain-language explanation of what IOB shows: Luna-delivered insulin
 * only, decision-support to avoid stacking, never instructs/changes a dose.
 * Lifted verbatim from `iob-display/settings-iob.html`.
 */
import TabBar from "../ios/TabBar.astro";
import Toggle from "../ios/Toggle.astro";

interface Props {
  variant?: "current" | "legacy";
}
---
<div class="content">
  {/* nav header: Moonlight back (to Settings) + "IOB Display", NO divider */}
  <div class="navbar">
    <button class="back" aria-label="Back to Settings">
      <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M15 18l-6-6 6-6"/></svg>
      Settings
    </button>
  </div>
  <div class="pad" style="padding-bottom:6px;">
    <div class="title-1" style="font-size:28px; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:-0.015em;">IOB Display</div>
  </div>

  <div class="pad" style="overflow-y:auto;">
    {/* THE TOGGLE — default OFF (opt-in) */}
    <div class="sec-label">Display</div>
    <div class="list">
      <div class="row explain">
        <span class="label-col">
          <span class="label">Show insulin on board</span>
          <span class="sub">Off by default. When on, your Home screen shows your active Luna insulin.</span>
        </span>
        <Toggle checked={false} label="Show insulin on board" />
      </div>
    </div>

    {/* PLAIN-LANGUAGE EXPLANATION — decision-support only. */}
    <div class="card-dark explain-card">
      <div class="lead">
        <span class="moon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="t">What this shows</span>
      </div>
      <p>Insulin on board (IOB) is how much of your <b style="color:var(--color-on-dark);">Luna-delivered insulin</b> is still active in your body. Seeing it can help you avoid stacking — taking more insulin on top of insulin that's still working.</p>
      <div class="ex-row">
        <span class="ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 2.7S5 9.5 5 14.5a7 7 0 0 0 14 0C19 9.5 12 2.7 12 2.7z"/></svg></span>
        <span class="x">Shows during an active Luna session, then carries the residual amount after the session ends until that insulin clears — e.g. <span class="sample">0.4&nbsp;<span class="u">U</span></span>.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="ex-row">
        <span class="ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/><path d="M12 8h.01M11 12h1v4h1"/></svg></span>
        <span class="x">Counts <b>Luna-delivered insulin only</b> — not insulin you deliver outside Luna.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="ex-row">
        <span class="ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 22a10 10 0 1 0 0-20 10 10 0 0 0 0 20zM12 16v-4M12 8h.01"/></svg></span>
        <span class="x">This is information to help you decide. Luna won't recommend, change, or deliver a dose based on it.</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="height:14px;"></div>
  </div>

  <div style="flex:1;"></div>
</div>

<TabBar active="settings" />
